<h1>About Me</h1>

<p>
Hi, I'm <strong>Kaybee</strong>, a technology professional based in Sweden with a passion for Cloud Computing, DevOps, Embedded Systems, and IoT.
</p>

<p>
My professional journey has always revolved around technology and solving problems. I started my career in IT Support before joining Booking.com, where I worked as both a Customer Support Specialist and later a Development Support Specialist, collaborating with customers, developers, and internal engineering teams to resolve complex technical issues.
</p>

<p>
Today, I work in Customer Operations at IAR, a global leader in embedded software development tools. Although my role is not an engineering position, working in this environment has strengthened my interest in embedded technologies and how they integrate with cloud platforms and modern software systems.
</p>

<p>
Alongside my professional career, I'm actively transitioning into Cloud and DevOps Engineering by building hands-on projects, studying Linux, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, and CI/CD pipelines while documenting everything I learn on this blog.
</p>

<h2>What I'm Building</h2>

<p>
I'm particularly interested in the intersection of Cloud Computing, Embedded Systems, and IoT. My long-term goal is to develop intelligent cloud-connected devices capable of solving real-world problems in agriculture, industrial automation, and smart infrastructure.
</p>

